Event Logistics

Location

The hackathon will be held in Room 204, Science Building. Enter through the main entrance, take the stairs or elevator to the second floor, and follow the signs to Room 204. Volunteers will be available to help with directions.

Food & Refreshments

  • Breakfast: Bagels, fruit, coffee, and juice (served at 8:30 AM)
  • Lunch: Pizza (vegetarian and meat options), salad, and drinks (served at 12:00 PM)
  • Snacks and drinks will be available throughout the day.

Event Hours

Participants are expected to attend from 8:30 AM to 5:00 PM. Please arrive on time for check-in and stay through the awards ceremony if possible.

Policy for Big Data Hackathon Participants

We understand that some students are also competing in the Big Data Hackathon, which partially overlaps with this event. If you are participating in both:

  • Please notify an organizer at check-in so we can coordinate your schedule.
  • You are permitted to step out for Big Data Hackathon commitments, but must inform your team and an organizer.
  • We encourage you to prioritize project submission deadlines for both events and communicate proactively with both teams.
